Product name: Snugglebumms - Princess Snuggleina Playskool 1985 Vintage Toy
Description:
*Item Details*
Vintage Snugglebumms Princess Sunggleina Toy, made by Playskool in 1985.
*Condition*
Princess Snuggleina comes with her original skirt and crown. The crown is attached by a clear plastic loop. She was a little grimy and musty when I found her - I suspect she'd been stored away in a loft. I've given her a gentle clean with a damp cloth, but left her hair well alone. There's a little bit of marking to the body, with some light scratches and there's some scuffing and wear to her gloves. Her wand/flower is also quite marked and scuffed. The paint on her heart is a little smudged at the top and there is minor wear to her face markings. The base of the toy is a bit worn and discoloured. The hair is a little discoloured in parts - mainly at the hairline. 
Since taking the photos, I've also given the skirt a handwash as it was dirty and it seems to have gotten out all the marks. The elastic in the skirt has gone and it is no longer stretchy, so you may wish to replace it.
She is missing her booklet and brush.

Product name: Vintage World Globe - Vintage Globe - Mid Century Globe Decor - Earth Globe - Desk Globe -Replogle Globe - Welch Scientific Tellurian Globe
Description:
This mid-century vintage Replogle globe is mounted on a rare Welch Scientific base designed by William A. Hall and referred to as the Hall Tellurian Globe having many functions similar to an orrery.  The metal base has an adjustable blue dial with constellations, zodiac signs, seasons, the months and days of the year.
The mount houses a 12 inch Replogle Reference Globe designed and edited by the cartographer Gustav Brueckmann.  The globe dates to the early 1950s and the beginning of the Cold War Era.   Vietnam is divided by north and south.  East Germany is marked "Soviet Zone." 
The globe is in good condition showing typical dust soiling, spots, and a few very small areas of paper loss.  The base dial is in beautiful condition.  However the mount is not complete.  It  has its full meridian indicating sun rise and sun set lines but is missing its steel ferules indicated night and day. 
Globe Diameter - 12 Inches
16 Inches Tall
8 1/8 Inch Base Diameter
Dial is marked "Copyright 1936 by William H. Hall"
Base has its original Welch Scientific foil label

Product name: Vintage Royal Doulton figurine Ascot, HN2356
Description:
I very fond of this figurine for the interesting face.  She is a calm, sophisticated woman, not a young thing, sitting casually in her Edwardian clothing on a wooden chair at the Ascot races.  She has her umbrella ready (you have to protect those big hats if it rains!), but doesn't need it yet. She is either watching the crowd or watching the horses, but she's certainly checking out something.  Perhaps she is comparing dress fashions.  Ascot was and still is THE Royal and fashionable race meeting.
Ascot was designed by  Mary Nicoll, and was produced between 1968 and 1995.
The book value is 250, which will probably start to rise soon, as she has been out of production for nearly 20 years now.  She is in mint condition.

Product name: Adam Bede by George Eliot, Vintage Book, 1952
Description:
Adam Bede by George Eliot, published by Collins in 1952 as part of the 'Collins Classics' series. 
The dust jacket has quite a bit of wear and tearing - mainly to the top edge and at the ends of the spine. There's wear to all the dust jacket edges, with several areas showing whitening, or chipping where the blue colour has worn away. There's some light scuffing to the dust jacket, as well as some fading along its top edges. The spine is quite faded and has a couple of creases along its length. The front and back fold-over flaps are creased at the top edges and show a strip of tanning at their folds. 
The book itself is bound in blue cloth with gilt lettering to the spine. There's a bit of shelf wear to the book edges, especially at the spine ends, and some fading along the top edges of the boards. The page edges are fairly clean, just a little denting and the top of the page edges (which are coloured blue) are a little faded and dented. There's some strong creasing at the bottom of pages 229-234, which would have occurred during manufacture. 
The front pastedown endpaper has a small bookseller's sticker at the bottom, which is hidden by the dust jacket flap and the front free endpaper has some writing impression marks at the top edge. There's a small crease to the half-title page at the top right corner and there's some light marking to the title page where ink from the author's portrait has bled onto it (this may just be visible in the third photograph). The letter to request a full list of other publications is also present - see the fourth photo.
Please get in touch if you have any questions, or if you require extra photos.

Product name: BumbleBee Spinning Wheel
Description:
New for 2016 we have moved the wheel to the back of the upright. This makes changing the drive band easier as well as changing the Whorl. Treadling is smoother as well.
We have re-invented the wheel!!  Our new "Patchwork Wheel" is designed to prevent warping. Four pieces are cleverly fitted together at right angles to each other creating the patchwork effect. Doing this has the grain of the wood running at 90 degrees to the other which is what will prevent warping. We still STRONGLY recommend that you finish your BumbleBee as soon as you can. 
Acting on customers and dealers suggestions we have made some changes to the BumbleBee. We have replaced the metal hinges on the treadle pedals with leather hinges. These work smoother, do not require frequent oiling to prevent squeaks, and keep the pedals in alignment better.  The height has also been increased by 1 in to allow for our jumbo bobbins to work on this spinning wheel. In addition we now put the company logo on the treadle pedals. The logo can also mean BumbleBee as well as BlueBonnet
You don't have to invest a fortune to learn to spin. This hardworking no nonsense spinning wheel is ideal for beginners. Intermediate spinners will be pleased with its 2 spinning ratios. This was designed to be primarily a beginners wheel at a price no one we have been able to find in the world can match for a new, solid hardwood, spinning wheel.
As with all our spinning wheels, the BumbleBee is made from solid hardwood. These are made from red oak. The spinning wheel has been sanded smooth and is ready for you to apply your choice of finish.  Wax, Danish Oil, or varnish will bring out the natural reddish color of the wood and really make the appearance of the grain show. We have found that Danish Oil is the best.
The wheel axle is on two sealed bearings for ease of treadling and the flyer axle also has two bearings for quiet operation. The bobbin is also on two sealed bearings for quiet operation. No other wheel offers sealed bearings at this price!
We do not use plywood or MDF on our spinning wheels. We want our wheels to be heirloom quality spinning wheels that will last for generations to come.
Included with your Bee is a basic instructional video which includes:
Assembly
How To Sit
Learning To Treadle
Changing a Bobbin
Threading The Flyer
Adjusting The Scotch Tension
Getting Started Spinning
Specifications:
28 inches tall
Orifice height is 27 inches
Delta orifice with sliding hook Flyer
6:1 and 8:1 spinning ratios
16 inch solid hardwood wheel
Solid hardwood frame
18 inch by 18 inch base occupies a small area but is exceptionally stable.
Assembly requires putting in 2 screws to fasten the upright and wheel to the base. Putting the footmen on, and putting the flyer assembly on. 10 minutes (maybe less!)
Double treadle for ease of operation
Single drive with Scotch Tension
Weighs approximately 14 pounds.
One bobbin (3.5 inches diameter x 4.25 inches long) is included.
Quick change flyer is the same flyer design used on our more expensive spinning wheels.
One Year Guarantee
All specifications subject to change without notice.
Full details of guarantee are on our website at www.bluebonnetwheels.com
We pack the spinning wheel for shipment very carefully and always insure it for full value.  We will not cover damage in transit. 
Contact us immediately if the spinning wheel arrives damaged and we will help you file a claim with the shipper.
We ship via FedEx to the contiguous United States.  Alaska and Hawaii will be sent US Mail at a cost of 45.00. We will invoice you through PayPal for the additional charge. We Do Not Ship Outside The United States.
